snippet: Swiss lender Raiffeisen is open to making acquisitions in private banking and asset management, potentially targeting firms handling assets of 20 billion to 30 billion Swiss francs (19.90 billion pounds), its chief was quoted as saying on Saturday...

headline.print_headline: Switzerland's Raiffeisen Eyes Firms Managing Assets Up to 20 Billion Pounds
headline.main: Switzerland's Raiffeisen Eyes Firms Managing Assets Up to 20 Billion Pounds

lead_paragraph: Swiss lender Raiffeisen is open to making acquisitions in private banking and asset management, potentially targeting firms handling assets of 20 billion to 30 billion Swiss francs (19.90 billion pounds), its chief was quoted as saying on Saturday.
